The paper discusses security-critical system requirements and access control systems, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for formal analysis methods and tools, which are often developed in the programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on the SELinux operating system, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
